!! Q: When should I use a facade vs raw mixins?

Use facades (`pills`, `vtabs`) for standard use cases — they handle all mixin wiring internally. Use raw mixins only when you need a completely new component type that doesn't fit either facade's rendering model.

!! Q: Why doesn't $slot work inside my \procedure?

This is a TiddlyWiki limitation. `$slot` inside `\procedure` cannot find `$fill` from an outer `$transclude $tiddler=` call. The workaround is to place `$slot` at body level (outside any procedure) with `<%if%>` branching. This is why vtabs inlines its render loop instead of using `core/menu.tid`.

!! Q: How do I add a new element type?

# Choose a type code (e.g., `mytype`)
# Add a view delegate in `core/mixins/bytype/view-delegate.tid` (or define `rrc1.elem-view:mytype` in your component)
# Add a click handler: `rrc1.elem-clicked:mytype`
# Add CSS for the type (class-prefixed, e.g., `.rrc-pills .rrc-elem-mytype`)
# If using vtabs, add an `<%if%>` branch and include the code in `visible-types`

!! Q: Why no @scope CSS?

`@scope` is Chrome-only as of early 2026. For cross-browser compatibility, the components use class-prefixed CSS (`.rrc-pills`, `.rrc-vtabs`) to scope styles.

!! Q: How do I sync component state to an external tiddler?

Use the `sync-tiddler` and `sync-field` parameters on pills. The component reads initial state from and writes selection changes to the specified tiddler field. For vtabs, the `state` parameter controls where the active tab state is stored.

